				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-652752/scp-1972#post-1777560</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 17 May 2013 17:31:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Djoric</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>388108</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>Lethal acid gun</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p>stream of superheated plasma with a temperature of approximately 30,000&#160;K</p> </blockquote> <p>Reading comprehension, my friend.</p> <p>The sphere has the personality of Judge Dredd and the volume control of a Dalek. If it didn't shoot lighting, we'd be having issues.</p> <p>It sees the Foundation as interfering with its mission, the punishment for which is a face fulla' lightning.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-652752#post-1777389</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-652752/scp-1972#post-1777389</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 17 May 2013 14:30:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>wishun</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1204404</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The intro to the first interview is missing the -A in a place or two.</p> <p>Aside from all the goodness already mentioned by others, I like the toss-off reference to orgone energy. That nutty psudo-science discredited nearly a century ago? Yeah, totally a real thing; and it's a big issue with the intergalactic community right now.</p> <p>Maybe they could get -B to calm down if they played to it's monomania. Tell it that the Foundation is the local relevant legal authority, it's almost true, and that -A is being indefinitely incarcerated pending investigation into further locally committed crimes. Depending on -B's reaction, they could expand the ploy to include -B being held pending resolution of charges of assault and officer misconduct.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
